<TITLE> Iran to France: sanctions won't stop atomic plans </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TEHRAN, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Iran will not abandon its right to nuclear technology regardless of threats of more sanctions, Foreign Minister Manouchehr Mottaki said in a letter to his French counterpart issued on Monday by an Iranian news agency. "Iran will not let its right to nuclear technology be suppressed ... Using tools like the Security Council, economic sanctions and other threats cannot deprive our nation and our government for a moment from its decision," he wrote to Bernard Kouchner in the letter published by ISNA news agency. He wrote that "unilateral sanctions", which Paris wants the European Union to implement against Iran, were illegal and violated the UN chart
